ioles (centrosomes) as &quot;The main function of the centriole is to help with cell division in animal cells...The second function of centrioles that we will focus on is ciliogenesis.&quot; (<a href=\"https://sites.google.com/a/asu.edu/the-almighty-cell/the-source/animal-cell/centriole\" rel=\"nofollow\">sites.google.com/a/asu.edu/the-almighty-cell/the-source/&hellip;<\/a>). A cell can survive rather easily without reproducing."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":0,"post_id":44139,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/kIqWF.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19099,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19099/another-homo-sapien","reputation":1004,"display_name":"another 'Homo sapien'"},"edited":false,"creation_date":1457605683,"comment_id":76687,"body":"@another&#39;Homosapien&#39; - I just rejected the edit; if you think centrioles are organelles it might need a reference. I&#39;m no expert, but I wouldn&#39;t regard that as an organelle? The core of this question is indeed &quot;what is an organelle&quot; - good point."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/kIqWF.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19099,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19099/another-homo-sapien","reputation":1004,"display_name":"another 'Homo sapien'"},"score":1,"post_id":44139,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"edited":false,"creation_date":1457605838,"comment_id":76689,"body":"@Christiaan &quot;A centriole is an ORGANELLE that helps cells divide, or make copies of themselves.&quot;